This article provides an update on the U.S. Government's response to the earthquake that struck Haiti in 2010. The United States has mobilized resources and personnel to aid in the relief effort, with USAID leading the coordination. Military personnel are playing a crucial role in supporting humanitarian efforts, including logistics and distribution of assistance. The U.S. is coordinating with the United Nations and over 30 nations to deliver food and water quickly throughout the country. The USNS Comfort, a hospital ship, has arrived in Haiti and is treating patients. The article also highlights the efforts in health/medical, airports/ports, safety/security, evacuation/rescues, food/water, adoptions, assistance provided, and ways to support relief efforts.